707412f-a.title: Brooklyn: Willow St. - Poplar St.
707412f-a.text:
(1)
1-11 Willow Street, east side, south from Poplar Street ; No. 1, at
Poplar Street, is invisible. Also seen is 21-23 Poplar Street, at the
foot of Willow Street, between Columbia Heights and Mc Kenney Street.
April 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same; showing only Nos. 1-3 Willow Street, with Poplar Street,
south side, east from Willow to Hicks Streets.
April 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

706304f-a.title: Brooklyn: Poplar Street - Willow Street
706304f-a.text:
Poplar Street, west from Willow Street to Columbia
Heights, where itterminates. The 3-story house, in the
center, is on the latter street. In the background is
the lower Manhattan skyline, the buildings (fror left to
right) being the City Bank Farmers Trust, the Bank of
Manhattan and the 60 Wall Tower.
About 1939
Gift of Dr. Michael Wishengrad, A. R. P. S.
